FTSE 100 Stocks Climb as Shares of Resolution, Burberry Advance in London

-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-06-07T07:22:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/ftse-100-stocks-climb-as-shares-of-resolution-burberry-advance-in-london.html
U.K. stocks climbed for a third day,
led by gains in  Resolution Ltd. (RSL)  and  Burberry Group Plc. (BRBY)   The FTSE 100 Index climbed 0.3 percent to 5,878.3 at 8:17
a.m. in London, after falling 0.2 percent earlier.  Resolution gained 2.9 percent to 308.6 pence after
announcing plans to buy back 250 million pounds ($410
million)worth of shares.  Burberry rallied 2.9 percent to 1,345 pence after La
Tribune reported that French luxury-goods company PPR SA is
planning a large acquisition in the high-fashion business.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  